0Entertainment%20Enterprises%20Limited%20during%20the%202018-19%20and%202019-20%20financial%20years.%20Furthermore%2C%20NFRA%20has%20imposed%20penalties%20on%20two%20chartered%20accountants%20(CA)%20-AB%20Jani%20and%20Rakesh%20Sharma%20-%20and%20barred%20them%20from%20work.%20While%20AB%20Jani%20has%20been%20fined%20Rs.%2010%20lakh%20and%20debarment%20for%20any%20audit%20work%20for%205%20years%2C%20Sharma%20has%20been%20fined%20Rs.%205%20lakh%20and%203%20years%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAB%20Jani%20was%20the%20Engagement%20Partner%20(EP)%2C%20and%20Rakesh%20Sharma%20was%20the%20Engagement%20Quality%20Control%20Review%20(EQCR)%20Partner%20for%20the%20company%20audit%20for%202018-19%20and%202019-%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Deloitte%20has%20come%20under%20scrutiny%20over%20lapses%20in%20audit.%20Here's%20a%20list%20of%20past%20cases%20on%20Deloitte%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeloitte%20Indonesia%20and%20Philippines%20Fined%20%242%20Million%20In%20Exam%20Cheating%20Case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20April%2C%20the%20Public%20Company%20Accounting%20Oversight%20Board%20(PCAOB)%20fined%20Deloitte%20Indonesia%20and%20Deloitte%20Philippines%20%241%20million%20each%20in%20an%20exam%20cheating%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpcaobus.org%2Fnews-events%2Fnews-releases%2Fnews-release-detail%2Fpcaob-imposes--2-million-in-fines-on-deloitte-indonesia-and-deloitte-philippines--bars-firm-leader-after-exam-cheating%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPCAOB's%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%202017%20to%202019%2C%20Deloitte%20Philippines's%20audit%20partners%20and%20other%20personnel%20engaged%20in%20widespread%20answer%20sharing.%20Wilfredo%20Baltazar%2C%20a%20former%20partner%20at%20Deloitte%20Philippines%20directly%20and%20substantially%20contributed%20to%20the%20firm's%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202021%20to%202023%2C%20more%20than%20200%20Deloitte%20Indonesia%20professionals%20engaged%20in%20answer%20sharing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20admitting%20or%20denying%20the%20findings%2C%20Deloitte%20Indonesia%2C%20Deloitte%20Philippines%2C%20and%20Baltazar%20consented%20to%20the%20PCAOB's%20respective%20orders%20against%20them.%20All%20were%20censured.%20While%20Deloitte%20Indonesia%20and%20Deloitte%20Philippines%20each%20agreed%20to%20pay%20a%20%241%20million%20civil%20money%20penalty%2C%20Baltazar%20agreed%20to%20pay%20a%20%2410%2C000%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2431%20Million%20Fine%20And%20A%20Suspension%20Notice%20In%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20China%20fined%20Deloitte%20211.9%20million%20yuan%20(%2430.8%20million)%20for%20failing%20to%20perform%20its%20duty%20in%20assessing%20the%20asset%20quality%20of%20China%20Huarong%20Asset%20Management%20Co%20Ltd.%20The%20government%20also%20suspended%20Deloitte's%20Beijing%20operations%20for%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20regret%20that%2C%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20the%20MOF%20considers%20certain%20aspects%20of%20our%20work%20fell%20below%20the%20required%20auditing%20standards%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Deloitte%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20published%20on%20its%20website%20and%20accepted%20the%20finance%20ministry's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%241.14%20Million%20Fine%20Over%20SIG%20Audit%20Failures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Financial%20Reporting%20Council%20(FRC)%20fined%20Deloitte%20over%20%C2%A3900%2C000%20(%241.14%20million)%20over%20failures%20in%20its%20audit%20of%20the%20building%20materials%20firm%20SIG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFRC%20also%20handed%20a%20fine%20of%20%C2%A336%2C250%20to%20Simon%20Manning%2C%20who%20was%20the%20audit%20engagement%20partner%20working%20on%20the%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw